{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":855,"text":"There is an entire genre of YouTube videos"},{"time":3798,"text":"devoted to an experience which"},{"time":5811,"text":"I am certain that everyone in this room has had."},{"time":8388,"text":"It entails an individual who,"},{"time":10401,"text":"thinking they're alone,"},{"time":11964,"text":"engages in some expressive behavior —"},{"time":15170,"text":"wild singing, gyrating dancing,"},{"time":17677,"text":"some mild sexual activity —"},{"time":20280,"text":"only to discover that, in fact, they are not alone,"},{"time":22878,"text":"that there is a person watching and lurking,"},{"time":25923,"text":"the discovery of which causes them"},{"time":27678,"text":"to immediately cease what they were doing"},{"time":29578,"text":"in horror."},{"time":31468,"text":"The sense of shame and humiliation"},{"time":33550,"text":"in their face is palpable."},{"time":35833,"text":"It's the sense of,"},{"time":37565,"text":"\"This is something I'm willing to do"},{"time":39298,"text":"only if no one else is watching.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":42898,"text":"This is the crux of the work"},{"time":45316,"text":"on which I have been singularly focused"},{"time":47363,"text":"for the last 16 months,"},{"time":49238,"text":"the question of why privacy matters,"},{"time":51300,"text":"a question that has arisen"},{"time":53238,"text":"in the context of a global debate,"},{"time":56360,"text":"enabled by the revelations of Edward Snowden"},{"time":58848,"text":"that the United States and its partners,"},{"time":61189,"text":"unbeknownst to the entire world,"},{"time":63211,"text":"has converted the Internet,"},{"time":65303,"text":"once heralded as an unprecedented tool"},{"time":68104,"text":"of liberation and democratization,"},{"time":71420,"text":"into an unprecedented zone"},{"time":73189,"text":"of mass, indiscriminate surveillance."}]},{"cues":[{"time":77283,"text":"There is a very common sentiment"},{"time":79240,"text":"that arises in this debate,"},{"time":80726,"text":"even among people who are uncomfortable"},{"time":82683,"text":"with mass surveillance, which says"},{"time":84737,"text":"that there is no real harm"},{"time":86660,"text":"that comes from this large-scale invasion"},{"time":89405,"text":"because only people who are engaged in bad acts"},{"time":92679,"text":"have a reason to want to hide"},{"time":94748,"text":"and to care about their privacy."},{"time":97459,"text":"This worldview is implicitly grounded"},{"time":100240,"text":"in the proposition that there are\ntwo kinds of people in the world,"},{"time":102416,"text":"good people and bad people."},{"time":104452,"text":"Bad people are those who plot terrorist attacks"},{"time":107420,"text":"or who engage in violent criminality"},{"time":108918,"text":"and therefore have reasons to\nwant to hide what they're doing,"},{"time":112070,"text":"have reasons to care about their privacy."},{"time":114127,"text":"But by contrast, good people"},{"time":116950,"text":"are people who go to work,"},{"time":118603,"text":"come home, raise their children, watch television."},{"time":121505,"text":"They use the Internet not to plot bombing attacks"},{"time":124261,"text":"but to read the news or exchange recipes"},{"time":126736,"text":"or to plan their kids' Little League games,"},{"time":129210,"text":"and those people are doing nothing wrong"},{"time":131528,"text":"and therefore have nothing to hide"},{"time":133575,"text":"and no reason to fear"},{"time":135937,"text":"the government monitoring them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":138379,"text":"The people who are actually saying that"},{"time":140189,"text":"are engaged in a very extreme act"},{"time":142968,"text":"of self-deprecation."},{"time":144524,"text":"What they're really saying is,"},{"time":146433,"text":"\"I have agreed to make myself"},{"time":148626,"text":"such a harmless and unthreatening"},{"time":151472,"text":"and uninteresting person that I actually don't fear"},{"time":154430,"text":"having the government know what it is that I'm doing.\""},{"time":157779,"text":"This mindset has found what I think"},{"time":159583,"text":"is its purest expression"},{"time":161652,"text":"in a 2009 interview with"},{"time":163959,"text":"the longtime CEO of Google, Eric Schmidt, who,"},{"time":166894,"text":"when asked about all the different ways his company"},{"time":169436,"text":"is causing invasions of privacy"},{"time":171608,"text":"for hundreds of millions of people around the world,"},{"time":174217,"text":"said this: He said,"},{"time":176208,"text":"\"If you're doing something that you don't want"},{"time":177884,"text":"other people to know,"},{"time":179898,"text":"maybe you shouldn't be doing it in the first place.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":183903,"text":"Now, there's all kinds of things to say about"},{"time":185888,"text":"that mentality,"},{"time":188233,"text":"the first of which is that the people who say that,"},{"time":191473,"text":"who say that privacy isn't really important,"},{"time":193588,"text":"they don't actually believe it,"},{"time":196535,"text":"and the way you know that\nthey don't actually believe it"},{"time":198357,"text":"is that while they say with their\nwords that privacy doesn't matter,"},{"time":201226,"text":"with their actions, they take all kinds of steps"},{"time":204387,"text":"to safeguard their privacy."},{"time":207154,"text":"They put passwords on their email"},{"time":208972,"text":"and their social media accounts,"},{"time":210742,"text":"they put locks on their bedroom"},{"time":212621,"text":"and bathroom doors,"},{"time":213970,"text":"all steps designed to prevent other people"},{"time":216670,"text":"from entering what they consider their private realm"},{"time":219572,"text":"and knowing what it is that they\ndon't want other people to know."},{"time":223273,"text":"The very same Eric Schmidt, the CEO of Google,"},{"time":226333,"text":"ordered his employees at Google"},{"time":228942,"text":"to cease speaking with the online"},{"time":230877,"text":"Internet magazine CNET"},{"time":233150,"text":"after CNET published an article"},{"time":235740,"text":"full of personal, private information"},{"time":237773,"text":"about Eric Schmidt,"},{"time":239854,"text":"which it obtained exclusively\nthrough Google searches"},{"time":242970,"text":"and using other Google products. (Laughter)"},{"time":246311,"text":"This same division can be seen"},{"time":248168,"text":"with the CEO of Facebook, Mark Zuckerberg,"},{"time":250630,"text":"who in an infamous interview in 2010"},{"time":254160,"text":"pronounced that privacy is no longer"},{"time":256559,"text":"a \"social norm.\""},{"time":259584,"text":"Last year, Mark Zuckerberg and his new wife"},{"time":262140,"text":"purchased not only their own house"},{"time":264445,"text":"but also all four adjacent houses in Palo Alto"},{"time":268320,"text":"for a total of 30 million dollars"},{"time":269934,"text":"in order to ensure that they enjoyed a zone of privacy"},{"time":273466,"text":"that prevented other people from monitoring"},{"time":275592,"text":"what they do in their personal lives."}]},{"cues":[{"time":279191,"text":"Over the last 16 months, as I've\ndebated this issue around the world,"},{"time":281944,"text":"every single time somebody has said to me,"},{"time":284360,"text":"\"I don't really worry about invasions of privacy"},{"time":285869,"text":"because I don't have anything to hide.\""},{"time":287478,"text":"I always say the same thing to them."},{"time":289178,"text":"I get out a pen, I write down my email address."},{"time":291471,"text":"I say, \"Here's my email address."},{"time":293113,"text":"What I want you to do when you get home"},{"time":294812,"text":"is email me the passwords"},{"time":296522,"text":"to all of your email accounts,"},{"time":298332,"text":"not just the nice, respectable work one in your name,"},{"time":300886,"text":"but all of them,"},{"time":302436,"text":"because I want to be able to just troll through"},{"time":304497,"text":"what it is you're doing online,"},{"time":306176,"text":"read what I want to read and\npublish whatever I find interesting."},{"time":308738,"text":"After all, if you're not a bad person,"},{"time":310538,"text":"if you're doing nothing wrong,"},{"time":312360,"text":"you should have nothing to hide.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":315340,"text":"Not a single person has taken me up on that offer."},{"time":318873,"text":"I check and — (Applause)"},{"time":322878,"text":"I check that email account religiously all the time."},{"time":326118,"text":"It's a very desolate place."},{"time":329323,"text":"And there's a reason for that,"},{"time":331110,"text":"which is that we as human beings,"},{"time":333151,"text":"even those of us who in words"},{"time":335105,"text":"disclaim the importance of our own privacy,"},{"time":337546,"text":"instinctively understand"},{"time":339683,"text":"the profound importance of it."},{"time":341877,"text":"It is true that as human beings, we're social animals,"},{"time":344704,"text":"which means we have a need for other people"},{"time":346853,"text":"to know what we're doing and saying and thinking,"},{"time":349597,"text":"which is why we voluntarily publish\ninformation about ourselves online."},{"time":353867,"text":"But equally essential to what it means"},{"time":356713,"text":"to be a free and fulfilled human being"},{"time":359294,"text":"is to have a place that we can go"},{"time":361431,"text":"and be free of the judgmental eyes of other people."},{"time":365459,"text":"There's a reason why we seek that out,"},{"time":367466,"text":"and our reason is that all of us —"},{"time":370376,"text":"not just terrorists and criminals, all of us —"},{"time":373704,"text":"have things to hide."},{"time":375749,"text":"There are all sorts of things that we do and think"},{"time":378496,"text":"that we're willing to tell our physician"},{"time":381197,"text":"or our lawyer or our psychologist or our spouse"},{"time":384952,"text":"or our best friend that we would be mortified"},{"time":387290,"text":"for the rest of the world to learn."},{"time":389250,"text":"We make judgments every single day"},{"time":391452,"text":"about the kinds of things that we say and think and do"},{"time":393910,"text":"that we're willing to have other people know,"},{"time":395631,"text":"and the kinds of things that we say and think and do"},{"time":397621,"text":"that we don't want anyone else to know about."},{"time":399950,"text":"People can very easily in words claim"},{"time":403277,"text":"that they don't value their privacy,"},{"time":405439,"text":"but their actions negate the authenticity of that belief."}]},{"cues":[{"time":410416,"text":"Now, there's a reason why privacy is so craved"},{"time":414146,"text":"universally and instinctively."},{"time":415890,"text":"It isn't just a reflexive movement"},{"time":417777,"text":"like breathing air or drinking water."},{"time":420491,"text":"The reason is that when we're in a state"},{"time":422931,"text":"where we can be monitored,\nwhere we can be watched,"},{"time":425588,"text":"our behavior changes dramatically."},{"time":428264,"text":"The range of behavioral options that we consider"},{"time":431297,"text":"when we think we're being watched"},{"time":433105,"text":"severely reduce."},{"time":435260,"text":"This is just a fact of human nature"},{"time":437475,"text":"that has been recognized in social science"},{"time":439763,"text":"and in literature and in religion"},{"time":441670,"text":"and in virtually every field of discipline."},{"time":443898,"text":"There are dozens of psychological studies"},{"time":446680,"text":"that prove that when somebody knows"},{"time":449231,"text":"that they might be watched,"},{"time":450800,"text":"the behavior they engage in"},{"time":452492,"text":"is vastly more conformist and compliant."},{"time":455974,"text":"Human shame is a very powerful motivator,"},{"time":459319,"text":"as is the desire to avoid it,"},{"time":462230,"text":"and that's the reason why people,"},{"time":463729,"text":"when they're in a state of\nbeing watched, make decisions"},{"time":465968,"text":"not that are the byproduct of their own agency"},{"time":469230,"text":"but that are about the expectations"},{"time":471242,"text":"that others have of them"},{"time":472694,"text":"or the mandates of societal orthodoxy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":477128,"text":"This realization was exploited most powerfully"},{"time":479995,"text":"for pragmatic ends by the 18th-\ncentury philosopher Jeremy Bentham,"},{"time":484136,"text":"who set out to resolve an important problem"},{"time":486487,"text":"ushered in by the industrial age,"},{"time":488289,"text":"where, for the first time, institutions had become"},{"time":490647,"text":"so large and centralized"},{"time":492644,"text":"that they were no longer able to monitor"},{"time":494472,"text":"and therefore control each one\nof their individual members,"},{"time":497425,"text":"and the solution that he devised"},{"time":499306,"text":"was an architectural design"},{"time":501509,"text":"originally intended to be implemented in prisons"},{"time":504225,"text":"that he called the panopticon,"},{"time":506544,"text":"the primary attribute of which was the construction"},{"time":508904,"text":"of an enormous tower in the center of the institution"},{"time":511975,"text":"where whoever controlled the institution"},{"time":514123,"text":"could at any moment watch any of the inmates,"},{"time":516808,"text":"although they couldn't watch all of them at all times."},{"time":520130,"text":"And crucial to this design"},{"time":522185,"text":"was that the inmates could not actually"},{"time":523980,"text":"see into the panopticon, into the tower,"},{"time":526856,"text":"and so they never knew"},{"time":528528,"text":"if they were being watched or even when."},{"time":530700,"text":"And what made him so excited about this discovery"},{"time":534283,"text":"was that that would mean that the prisoners"},{"time":536156,"text":"would have to assume that they were being watched"},{"time":539184,"text":"at any given moment,"},{"time":540869,"text":"which would be the ultimate enforcer"},{"time":542747,"text":"for obedience and compliance."},{"time":546425,"text":"The 20th-century French philosopher Michel Foucault"},{"time":549350,"text":"realized that that model could be used"},{"time":551275,"text":"not just for prisons but for every institution"},{"time":554390,"text":"that seeks to control human behavior:"},{"time":556340,"text":"schools, hospitals, factories, workplaces."},{"time":559215,"text":"And what he said was that this mindset,"},{"time":561413,"text":"this framework discovered by Bentham,"},{"time":563839,"text":"was the key means of societal control"},{"time":567168,"text":"for modern, Western societies,"},{"time":569170,"text":"which no longer need"},{"time":570944,"text":"the overt weapons of tyranny —"},{"time":572851,"text":"punishing or imprisoning or killing dissidents,"},{"time":575247,"text":"or legally compelling loyalty to a particular party —"},{"time":578561,"text":"because mass surveillance creates"},{"time":580960,"text":"a prison in the mind"},{"time":583515,"text":"that is a much more subtle"},{"time":585358,"text":"though much more effective means"},{"time":587247,"text":"of fostering compliance with social norms"},{"time":590296,"text":"or with social orthodoxy,"},{"time":591758,"text":"much more effective"},{"time":593320,"text":"than brute force could ever be."}]},{"cues":[{"time":596445,"text":"The most iconic work of literature about surveillance"},{"time":599263,"text":"and privacy is the George Orwell novel \"1984,\""},{"time":602813,"text":"which we all learn in school, and\ntherefore it's almost become a cliche."},{"time":606280,"text":"In fact, whenever you bring it up\nin a debate about surveillance,"},{"time":608349,"text":"people instantaneously dismiss it"},{"time":610598,"text":"as inapplicable, and what they say is,"},{"time":612900,"text":"\"Oh, well in '1984,' there were\nmonitors in people's homes,"},{"time":616183,"text":"they were being watched at every given moment,"},{"time":618348,"text":"and that has nothing to do with\nthe surveillance state that we face.\""},{"time":622310,"text":"That is an actual fundamental misapprehension"},{"time":625230,"text":"of the warnings that Orwell issued in \"1984.\""},{"time":627931,"text":"The warning that he was issuing"},{"time":629582,"text":"was about a surveillance state"},{"time":631190,"text":"not that monitored everybody at all times,"},{"time":633354,"text":"but where people were aware that they could"},{"time":635407,"text":"be monitored at any given moment."},{"time":637036,"text":"Here is how Orwell's narrator, Winston Smith,"},{"time":640110,"text":"described the surveillance system"},{"time":642150,"text":"that they faced:"},{"time":643548,"text":"\"There was, of course, no way of knowing"},{"time":645975,"text":"whether you were being watched\nat any given moment.\""},{"time":648292,"text":"He went on to say,"},{"time":649743,"text":"\"At any rate, they could plug in your wire"},{"time":651454,"text":"whenever they wanted to."},{"time":653163,"text":"You had to live, did live,"},{"time":655742,"text":"from habit that became instinct,"},{"time":657995,"text":"in the assumption that every sound you made"},{"time":660490,"text":"was overheard and except in darkness"},{"time":662680,"text":"every movement scrutinized.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":665419,"text":"The Abrahamic religions similarly posit"},{"time":668765,"text":"that there's an invisible, all-knowing authority"},{"time":671708,"text":"who, because of its omniscience,"},{"time":673451,"text":"always watches whatever you're doing,"},{"time":675347,"text":"which means you never have a private moment,"},{"time":678120,"text":"the ultimate enforcer"},{"time":679804,"text":"for obedience to its dictates."}]},{"cues":[{"time":682794,"text":"What all of these seemingly disparate works"},{"time":686198,"text":"recognize, the conclusion that they all reach,"},{"time":688984,"text":"is that a society in which people"},{"time":691306,"text":"can be monitored at all times"},{"time":693613,"text":"is a society that breeds conformity"},{"time":696268,"text":"and obedience and submission,"},{"time":698510,"text":"which is why every tyrant,"},{"time":700021,"text":"the most overt to the most subtle,"},{"time":702103,"text":"craves that system."},{"time":704366,"text":"Conversely, even more importantly,"},{"time":707020,"text":"it is a realm of privacy,"},{"time":709460,"text":"the ability to go somewhere where we can think"},{"time":712470,"text":"and reason and interact and speak"},{"time":715628,"text":"without the judgmental eyes\nof others being cast upon us,"},{"time":719282,"text":"in which creativity and exploration"},{"time":722825,"text":"and dissent exclusively reside,"},{"time":725853,"text":"and that is the reason why,"},{"time":727674,"text":"when we allow a society to exist"},{"time":730250,"text":"in which we're subject to constant monitoring,"},{"time":732413,"text":"we allow the essence of human freedom"},{"time":735390,"text":"to be severely crippled."}]},{"cues":[{"time":738341,"text":"The last point I want to observe about this mindset,"},{"time":741463,"text":"the idea that only people who \nare doing something wrong"},{"time":743388,"text":"have things to hide and therefore\nreasons to care about privacy,"},{"time":747270,"text":"is that it entrenches two very destructive messages,"},{"time":751276,"text":"two destructive lessons,"},{"time":753304,"text":"the first of which is that"},{"time":755060,"text":"the only people who care about privacy,"},{"time":757180,"text":"the only people who will seek out privacy,"},{"time":759236,"text":"are by definition bad people."},{"time":763311,"text":"This is a conclusion that we should have"},{"time":765443,"text":"all kinds of reasons for avoiding,"},{"time":767971,"text":"the most important of which is that when you say,"},{"time":770723,"text":"\"somebody who is doing bad things,\""},{"time":773100,"text":"you probably mean things\nlike plotting a terrorist attack"},{"time":775937,"text":"or engaging in violent criminality,"},{"time":777978,"text":"a much narrower conception"},{"time":780518,"text":"of what people who wield power mean"},{"time":782970,"text":"when they say, \"doing bad things.\""},{"time":785020,"text":"For them, \"doing bad things\" typically means"},{"time":787327,"text":"doing something that poses meaningful challenges"},{"time":790398,"text":"to the exercise of our own power."}]},{"cues":[{"time":793503,"text":"The other really destructive"},{"time":795453,"text":"and, I think, even more insidious lesson"},{"time":797361,"text":"that comes from accepting this mindset"},{"time":800140,"text":"is there's an implicit bargain"},{"time":802906,"text":"that people who accept this mindset have accepted,"},{"time":806250,"text":"and that bargain is this:"},{"time":807705,"text":"If you're willing to render yourself"},{"time":809677,"text":"sufficiently harmless,"},{"time":811779,"text":"sufficiently unthreatening"},{"time":813949,"text":"to those who wield political power,"},{"time":815831,"text":"then and only then can you be free"},{"time":818867,"text":"of the dangers of surveillance."},{"time":820975,"text":"It's only those who are dissidents,"},{"time":823360,"text":"who challenge power,"},{"time":824841,"text":"who have something to worry about."},{"time":826653,"text":"There are all kinds of reasons why we\nshould want to avoid that lesson as well."},{"time":830060,"text":"You may be a person who, right now,"},{"time":832298,"text":"doesn't want to engage in that behavior,"},{"time":834370,"text":"but at some point in the future you might."},{"time":836825,"text":"Even if you're somebody who decides"},{"time":838499,"text":"that you never want to,"},{"time":840264,"text":"the fact that there are other people"},{"time":841898,"text":"who are willing to and able to resist"},{"time":844102,"text":"and be adversarial to those in power —"},{"time":846136,"text":"dissidents and journalists"},{"time":847670,"text":"and activists and a whole range of others —"},{"time":849758,"text":"is something that brings us all collective good"},{"time":852252,"text":"that we should want to preserve."},{"time":855230,"text":"Equally critical is that the measure"},{"time":857324,"text":"of how free a society is"},{"time":859587,"text":"is not how it treats its good,"},{"time":861737,"text":"obedient, compliant citizens,"},{"time":864200,"text":"but how it treats its dissidents"},{"time":866040,"text":"and those who resist orthodoxy."},{"time":869155,"text":"But the most important reason"},{"time":870752,"text":"is that a system of mass surveillance"},{"time":873153,"text":"suppresses our own freedom in all sorts of ways."},{"time":875770,"text":"It renders off-limits"},{"time":877571,"text":"all kinds of behavioral choices"},{"time":879577,"text":"without our even knowing that it's happened."},{"time":883130,"text":"The renowned socialist activist Rosa Luxemburg"},{"time":885612,"text":"once said, \"He who does not move"},{"time":888105,"text":"does not notice his chains.\""},{"time":891461,"text":"We can try and render the chains"},{"time":893150,"text":"of mass surveillance invisible or undetectable,"},{"time":896239,"text":"but the constraints that it imposes on us"},{"time":898905,"text":"do not become any less potent."}]},{"cues":[{"time":901450,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":903058,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":904489,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":905996,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":910893,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":913280,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":919320,"text":"Bruno Giussani: Glenn, thank you."},{"time":921612,"text":"The case is rather convincing, I have to say,"},{"time":923901,"text":"but I want to bring you back"},{"time":925466,"text":"to the last 16 months and to Edward Snowden"},{"time":928817,"text":"for a few questions, if you don't mind."},{"time":930882,"text":"The first one is personal to you."},{"time":933370,"text":"We have all read about the arrest of your partner,"},{"time":936411,"text":"David Miranda in London, and other difficulties,"},{"time":939721,"text":"but I assume that"},{"time":941805,"text":"in terms of personal engagement and risk,"},{"time":945161,"text":"that the pressure on you is not that easy"},{"time":946965,"text":"to take on the biggest sovereign \norganizations in the world."},{"time":949910,"text":"Tell us a little bit about that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":952345,"text":"Glenn Greenwald: You know, I think\none of the things that happens"},{"time":954000,"text":"is that people's courage in this regard"},{"time":955932,"text":"gets contagious,"},{"time":957644,"text":"and so although I and the other\njournalists with whom I was working"},{"time":961107,"text":"were certainly aware of the risk —"},{"time":962643,"text":"the United States continues to be\nthe most powerful country in the world"},{"time":965365,"text":"and doesn't appreciate it when you"},{"time":967363,"text":"disclose thousands of their secrets"},{"time":969285,"text":"on the Internet at will —"},{"time":971796,"text":"seeing somebody who is a 29-year-old"},{"time":975265,"text":"ordinary person who grew up in"},{"time":977284,"text":"a very ordinary environment"},{"time":979597,"text":"exercise the degree of principled\ncourage that Edward Snowden risked,"},{"time":983320,"text":"knowing that he was going to go\nto prison for the rest of his life"},{"time":985540,"text":"or that his life would unravel,"},{"time":987322,"text":"inspired me and inspired other journalists"},{"time":989297,"text":"and inspired, I think, people around the world,"},{"time":991120,"text":"including future whistleblowers,"},{"time":992808,"text":"to realize that they can engage\nin that kind of behavior as well."}]},{"cues":[{"time":996323,"text":"BG: I'm curious about your\nrelationship with Ed Snowden,"},{"time":998809,"text":"because you have spoken with him a lot,"},{"time":1001990,"text":"and you certainly continue doing so,"},{"time":1003753,"text":"but in your book, you never call him Edward,"},{"time":1006389,"text":"nor Ed, you say \"Snowden.\" How come?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1009849,"text":"GG: You know, I'm sure that's something"},{"time":1011493,"text":"for a team of psychologists to examine.\n(Laughter)"},{"time":1014824,"text":"I don't really know. The reason I think that,"},{"time":1018413,"text":"one of the important objectives that he actually had,"},{"time":1021967,"text":"one of his, I think, most important tactics,"},{"time":1024303,"text":"was that he knew that one of the ways"},{"time":1026510,"text":"to distract attention from the\nsubstance of the revelations"},{"time":1029200,"text":"would be to try and personalize the focus on him,"},{"time":1031850,"text":"and for that reason, he stayed out of the media."},{"time":1033917,"text":"He tried not to ever have his personal life"},{"time":1036426,"text":"subject to examination,"},{"time":1038105,"text":"and so I think calling him Snowden"},{"time":1040819,"text":"is a way of just identifying him\nas this important historical actor"},{"time":1044393,"text":"rather than trying to personalize him in a way"},{"time":1046265,"text":"that might distract attention from the substance."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1049145,"text":"Moderator: So his revelations, your analysis,"},{"time":1050602,"text":"the work of other journalists,"},{"time":1052378,"text":"have really developed the debate,"},{"time":1055378,"text":"and many governments, for example, have reacted,"},{"time":1057506,"text":"including in Brazil, with projects and programs"},{"time":1060110,"text":"to reshape a little bit the design of the Internet, etc."},{"time":1062964,"text":"There are a lot of things going on in that sense."},{"time":1065716,"text":"But I'm wondering, for you personally,"},{"time":1067986,"text":"what is the endgame?"},{"time":1069637,"text":"At what point will you think,"},{"time":1071270,"text":"well, actually, we've succeeded \nin moving the dial?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1074462,"text":"GG: Well, I mean, the endgame for me as a journalist"},{"time":1076740,"text":"is very simple, which is to make sure"},{"time":1079183,"text":"that every single document that's newsworthy"},{"time":1081195,"text":"and that ought to be disclosed"},{"time":1082841,"text":"ends up being disclosed,"},{"time":1084321,"text":"and that secrets that should never\nhave been kept in the first place"},{"time":1086358,"text":"end up uncovered."},{"time":1087833,"text":"To me, that's the essence of journalism"},{"time":1089680,"text":"and that's what I'm committed to doing."},{"time":1091207,"text":"As somebody who finds mass surveillance odious"},{"time":1093681,"text":"for all the reasons I just talked about and a lot more,"},{"time":1095868,"text":"I mean, I look at this as work that will never end"},{"time":1098394,"text":"until governments around the world"},{"time":1100571,"text":"are no longer able to subject entire populations"},{"time":1103190,"text":"to monitoring and surveillance"},{"time":1104676,"text":"unless they convince some court or some entity"},{"time":1107265,"text":"that the person they've targeted"},{"time":1108987,"text":"has actually done something wrong."},{"time":1111578,"text":"To me, that's the way that\nprivacy can be rejuvenated."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1114813,"text":"BG: So Snowden is very,\nas we've seen at TED,"},{"time":1117159,"text":"is very articulate in presenting and portraying himself"},{"time":1119927,"text":"as a defender of democratic values"},{"time":1122207,"text":"and democratic principles."},{"time":1123920,"text":"But then, many people really \nfind it difficult to believe"},{"time":1126948,"text":"that those are his only motivations."},{"time":1129350,"text":"They find it difficult to believe"},{"time":1130828,"text":"that there was no money involved,"},{"time":1132449,"text":"that he didn't sell some of those secrets,"},{"time":1134360,"text":"even to China and to Russia,"},{"time":1136189,"text":"which are clearly not the best friends"},{"time":1138733,"text":"of the United States right now."},{"time":1140902,"text":"And I'm sure many people in the room"},{"time":1142608,"text":"are wondering the same question."},{"time":1144878,"text":"Do you consider it possible there is"},{"time":1146761,"text":"that part of Snowden we've not seen yet?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1149373,"text":"GG: No, I consider that absurd and idiotic."},{"time":1152554,"text":"(Laughter) If you wanted to,"},{"time":1154968,"text":"and I know you're just playing devil's advocate,"},{"time":1157430,"text":"but if you wanted to sell"},{"time":1160641,"text":"secrets to another country,"},{"time":1162547,"text":"which he could have done and become"},{"time":1164264,"text":"extremely rich doing so,"},{"time":1165910,"text":"the last thing you would \ndo is take those secrets"},{"time":1167891,"text":"and give them to journalists and\nask journalists to publish them,"},{"time":1170635,"text":"because it makes those secrets worthless."},{"time":1172661,"text":"People who want to enrich themselves"},{"time":1174309,"text":"do it secretly by selling \nsecrets to the government,"},{"time":1176279,"text":"but I think there's one important point worth making,"},{"time":1178100,"text":"which is, that accusation comes from"},{"time":1180338,"text":"people in the U.S. government,"},{"time":1182170,"text":"from people in the media who are loyalists"},{"time":1184190,"text":"to these various governments,"},{"time":1185788,"text":"and I think a lot of times when people make accusations like that about other people —"},{"time":1188936,"text":"\"Oh, he can't really be doing this"},{"time":1190541,"text":"for principled reasons,"},{"time":1192206,"text":"he must have some corrupt, nefarious reason\" —"},{"time":1194448,"text":"they're saying a lot more about themselves"},{"time":1196555,"text":"than they are the target of their accusations,"},{"time":1198381,"text":"because — (Applause) —"},{"time":1202766,"text":"those people, the ones who make that accusation,"},{"time":1205286,"text":"they themselves never act"},{"time":1207190,"text":"for any reason other than corrupt reasons,"},{"time":1209112,"text":"so they assume"},{"time":1210744,"text":"that everybody else is plagued by the same disease"},{"time":1213376,"text":"of soullessness as they are,"},{"time":1215378,"text":"and so that's the assumption."},{"time":1217249,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1218876,"text":"BG: Glenn, thank you very much.\nGG: Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1221360,"text":"BG: Glenn Greenwald."},{"time":1223692,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}